docs/tutorial/indexes.md:29:In general, an **index** is just something we can have to help us **find things faster**. It normally works by having things in **order**. Let's think about some real-life examples before even thinking about databases and code.
docs/tutorial/indexes.md:37:<img src="/img/tutorial/indexes/dictionary001.drawio.svg">
docs/tutorial/indexes.md:41:<img src="/img/tutorial/indexes/dictionary002.drawio.svg">
